Fifteen people have died in an  accident involving two minibus taxis transporting pupils to school and a heavy vehicle on the R579 in Motetema, Limpopo. The provincial  department of transport and community safety said  emergency services were  processing the scene and trying to free those trapped in the  wreckage. The cause of the crash was not immediately clear. “The road remains temporarily closed. Motorists are advised to use alternative routes or exercise patience if unable to change the route,” said the department. TimesLIVE